<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[491,1527,627,960]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">
Diagnosis (Female) — Prodorsum mostly smooth centrally, strongly reticulate laterally with large cells posteriorly and smaller cells anteriorly, setae short, serrate; opisthosoma between setae 
<emphasis box="[552,577,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">c1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[631,656,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">e1</emphasis>
weakly reticulate to weakly wrinkled, cuticle between and posterior to setae 
<emphasis box="[491,516,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">e1</emphasis>
with short transverse folds, setae 
<emphasis box="[879,899,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">f2</emphasis>
absent, with marginal setae short, serrate and 3 pairs of dorsocentral setae apparently smooth (
<figureCitation box="[909,994,765,789]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="10.[119,186,1853,1874]" captionTargetBox="[278,1367,337,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[231,1367,329,1799]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 6 Brevipalpus obovatusDonnadieu – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399542/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Fig 6A</figureCitation>
); genital and ventral shields colliculate (having small elevations) (
<figureCitation box="[689,773,799,823]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="10.[119,186,1853,1874]" captionTargetBox="[278,1367,337,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[231,1367,329,1799]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 6 Brevipalpus obovatusDonnadieu – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399542/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Fig 6B</figureCitation>
); rostrum extends to about middle of femur I; palp tarsus II with one solenidion distally; spermatheca terminates into a round vesicle with short finger-like projections around entire perimeter (
<figureCitation box="[883,966,868,892]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="10.[119,186,1853,1874]" captionTargetBox="[278,1367,337,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[231,1367,329,1799]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 6 Brevipalpus obovatusDonnadieu – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399542/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Fig 6C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[491,1527,627,960]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">
Deutonymph — Prodorsum with setae 
<emphasis box="[948,1005,902,926]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">sc1-2</emphasis>
short but clearly longer than 
<emphasis box="[1320,1345,902,926]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">v2</emphasis>
, opisthosoma also with setae short but 
<emphasis box="[755,866,936,960]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">c1, d1, d3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[911,936,936,960]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">e1</emphasis>
shorter than 
<emphasis box="[1076,1101,936,960]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">c3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1114,1140,936,960]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">e3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1153,1235,936,960]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">f3, h1-2</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1250,1335,936,960]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="10.[119,186,1853,1874]" captionTargetBox="[278,1367,337,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[231,1367,329,1799]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 6 Brevipalpus obovatusDonnadieu – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399542/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Fig 6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
